Early every morning, you could hear the miners walking to work along the paths to the local pits.They left for the first shift at 5.00 am, and returned home at 2.00 pm.Then they washed in their tin baths in front of the fire,and later worked in their allotments,where they grew all their own vegetables. Paulton was much smaller.There was a population of about 900.There were more farms .
